message.content: The likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are "cs.CL", "cs.AI", "cs.LG", "cs.IR", and "cs.NE". This is because the paper discusses the state-of-the-art solutions for Question Answering (QA) systems, which are typically based on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. These techniques are commonly used in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of LIME, which is a popular ML framework for explaining black-box models, further supporting the relevance of CS sub-categories related to ML and NLP.
